<h4>Field Courses in Environmental Science</h4>




<p>The department sponsors field trips that range in length from one day to several weeks. Shorter field trips typically form part of lecture-based courses and are offered each year. (The trips are open to all students and faculty if space permits.) Longer trips are designed as undergraduate field courses, and one such course may be used as an elective science course for the major. Destinations of field courses have recently included Baja California and the Bahamas<a href="/thecollege/geophysicalsciences/#_msocom_1">.</a></p>




